tags: insane amount of respect for the team behind creating the stage
body:
The stage

I was watching the tour movie again and I was like imagine the insane amount of effort in creating the stage; the design, the screens, the entrances and exits, the screens which move to create entrances and exits, the amount of material in building the stage, the construction/deconstruction of the stage, space for the band to play. IT’S MIND-BLOWING. imagine how many nooks and crannies there are in the stage like during the bad blood/ should’ve said no performance. 🤯🤯🤯

summary: Hi @taylorswift my name is Phoebe, I’m 16 years old (17 soon) and I have chronic fatigue. I was diagnosed around this time last...
body: Hi @taylorswift my name is Phoebe, I’m 16 years old (17 soon) and I have chronic fatigue. I was diagnosed around this time last year which was when it started to get much worse, but we think I’ve had it since I was around 9 years old. I just wanted to send you a HUUUUGGEEEE thank you for helping me through this! I started treatment June last year and it’s been hard because people don’t always believe it’s a thing as it’s an invisible disability but things are finally starting to look up and I’m getting better! Thank you for always being there for me whenever it all felt like hard work, thank you for being my shoulder to cry on whenever things got a little too much for me! Thank you for giving me songs to shout at the top of my lungs to on the long car journeys to my treatment! Thank you for giving me things to look forward to! Thank you for everything! For the 9 years you’ve been in my life thank you!!! I love you @taylorswift so much and I am so greateful to have you💛✨
